## MULTI-TENANT ARCHITECTURE				
Organization (Tenant/Client) → Account (Business Unit) → Department → User				
- **Hierarchy validation (mandatory)**: **Account** must belong to **Organization**; **Department** must belong to **Account**; **User** must belong to **Department** — enforce on create/update via **`HierarchyValidator`** (`backend/src/common/validators/hierarchy.validator.ts`)				
- **Tenant admin dashboard**: tree view of **Org → Accounts → Departments → Users** with **counts at each level** — **`GET /api/v1/organization/hierarchy`** (JWT org scope, **`org_admin`**)				
- **User** belongs to **Department** (and therefore **`account_id`** + **`org_id`**); **role** and **permissions** govern access; credentials stored as **`password_hash`** only				
- **Department** belongs to **Account** (and therefore **`org_id`** + **`account_id`**); **OKRs** are assigned at **department** level				
- **Account** belongs to **Organization** (`org_id`); **budget** is modeled per account (**credit_limit**, **allocated_credits**, **used_credits**); **multiple accounts per organization**				
- org_id is the PRIMARY tenant isolation key				
- EVERY document MUST have org_id				
- NEVER trust org_id from request body - extract from JWT				
- **Hierarchy REST**: `/organizations` (platform admin bearer `PLATFORM_ADMIN_TOKEN`); **`/accounts`**, **`/departments`**, **`/users`** require **`Authorization: Bearer <JWT>`** with **`org_id`** claim → **`tenantMiddleware`** sets **`req.tenantId`** (reject mismatched `org_id` query); **`X-User-Role`** enforces minimum role per route — replace header with JWT claims in production				
				
## BASE SCHEMA (Every MongoDB Collection)				
{				
  org_id: ObjectId,        // REQUIRED - tenant isolation				
  account_id?: ObjectId,   // For account-scoped resources				
  department_id?: ObjectId,// For dept-scoped resources				
  created_by: ObjectId,				
  created_at: Date,				
  updated_by: ObjectId,				
  updated_at: Date,				
  is_deleted: boolean,				
  _version: number				
}				
				
## SECURITY RULES (NEVER VIOLATE)				
1. org_id from JWT, NEVER from request body				
2. ALL queries include { org_id: req.tenantId, is_deleted: false }				
3. Audit log ALL mutations				
4. Validate ALL inputs with Joi/Zod				
5. Encrypt sensitive fields (credentials, tokens, PII)				
				
